This mosque is an important part of Hindu civilization and even today it is one of the most attractive mosques in India.  Masjid-e-Quba is located on Kishor Ki Bhagbaazi Marg and derives its name from the fact that the place is on Kishore Ki Bhagbazi Marg.  Masjid-e-Quba was built by Shah Jahan Shah who was a great ruler of Uttar Pradesh.
